v:4 c:$ m:T05-glass-editor-chrome role:dev x:vue3/css
gate: LOCKED

task: Harmonize the piano-roll editor chrome with the glass system; keep the working surface crisp

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/styles/logic-pro.css

context: |
  The piano-roll editor (.piano-roll-editor) already has ad-hoc glass inline in
  logic-pro.css (background rgba(30,30,34,.55) + blur 16px). The toolbar
  (.lp-editor-toolbar) and tool cluster (.lp-editor-tools) are partly there.
  GOAL: make the editor CHROME (toolbar, tool buttons, key-column gaps) cohere
  with glass.css tokens, but the WORKING SURFACE must stay crisp and opaque:

    CRISP / OPAQUE (do NOT glass-ify — these are precision work surfaces):
      - .lp-roll-grid-canvas, .lp-roll-ruler-canvas, .lp-roll-velocity-canvas
      - .lp-roll-keys piano keys (white/black gradients)
      - .lp-roll-keys-bg key column
    GLASS CHROME (harmonize):
      - .piano-roll-editor outer frame
      - .lp-editor-toolbar
      - .lp-editor-tools / .lp-editor-tool buttons

steps:
  1. .piano-roll-editor: re-point its hard-coded blur/borders to glass.css tokens
     (var(--glass-bg), var(--glass-border), var(--glass-highlight)) so it matches
     sidebar/transport instead of using one-off rgba values.
  2. .lp-editor-toolbar: same token alignment; inset highlight on top edge.
  3. .lp-editor-tool.active: use violet accent (T02 token), not the old #4a6fa5.
  4. EXPLICITLY ensure the grid/ruler/velocity canvases and the key column keep
     solid opaque backgrounds (no backdrop-filter on them) — verify no glass
     class leaks onto them. The piano keys must stay high-contrast/crisp.
  5. .lp-roll-keys-ruler-gap / -velocity-gap: may take a subtle frosted tint to
     bridge chrome→surface, but the key labels must stay legible.

deps: T02 (accent token for editor-tool.active).

done:
  - Editor frame + toolbar + tool buttons use glass.css tokens (cohesive material).
  - Active editor tool is violet accent.
  - Canvases and piano keys remain crisp/opaque (NO backdrop-filter on them).
  - Microtonal matrix-pad styling (PianoRollView scoped) still works.
  - Compiles; no CSS errors.
